{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"ad9a70b807504031","type":"file","file":"Sims4-Yootz-Story/Chapters/2.04-TalkToVampires.md","x":-948,"y":-4560,"width":780,"height":4840},
		{"id":"d977b64818765b81","type":"text","text":"Sara rushed past the stairs, though the one lone door,\n\n![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-16-26_11-07-00%20AM.png)\n\nand barely made it in time before her stomach started forcing everything up. \n\n![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-16-26_1-52-19%20PM.png)\n\nWhen the vomiting stopped long enough for Sara to get down on her knees, she held her belly with her left hand while she gripped the seat with her right to help keep herself up. More had already come up than she had expected, but she knew the feeling in her gut: it wasn't done. \n\nSara tried to breath at least a few breaths while she could. As she sat there on the floor, she found her mind going to how Don always said the pain was temporary and part of the process. \n\nUntil her stomach seized with a pain that cleared all thought from her mind and forced up even more from her stomach. \n\n----\n\nShe lost count of how many times that pain came back, and only knew that it got worse each time. \n\n![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-16-26_11-09-47%20AM.png)\n\nEven once it just turned into dry heaving and nothing really came out anymore, that pain deep in her gut kept intensifying. \n\n----\n\nWhen it finally did stop, just about every muscle in her core hurt. She used the edge of the sink to help pull herself up. \n\n![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-18-26_2-34-17%20PM.png)\n\nShe was shaky on her feet, and held the edges of sink to help steady herself. After a breath, she used some water to rinse her mouth out. As she spit it back into the sink, a certain calm settled over her. If she closed her eyes, she could pretend she was at the gym locker room after a workout. All the pain in her stomach had vanished. Sure, her abs hurt and the muscles in her legs were weak, but all of that was familiar. And probably just needed a little hydration and time. \n\nSara sighed at her own thoughts, and then raised her head to look at herself in the mirror. She didn't know **how** she knew it was all true, but she could feel it in her bones: not only were vampires real, she now was one. \n\nShe made sure her mouth was rinsed out, the sink was rinsed clean, and the toilet was flushed before she headed back out to the other room. ","x":-948,"y":540,"width":780,"height":2777},
		{"id":"2134156319b34a13","type":"text","text":"Maybe the pain is gone, maybe is really different now? But she still thinks she needs to keep down the food. \n\nShe doesn't, she can't. She's wrong about what her body needs, but I guess I'm thinking that her thoughts have some input over this, or rather her effort to calm herself is at least delaying the gut purge? She using things like breathing to manage physical activation at this point. \n\nBut later when her mind is spinning, not only is she not calming herself, some part of her knows she doesn't need the food. Idk if her thirst is playing a role in this, and it's taking a bit to come online and push the food out of the way? I mean when babies are born for example they need a lot more to drink relative to their size because their kidneys are still learning how to properly retain fluid. I guess I'm kind of comparing this to like that, where this is all new for her body. Like yeah it's finished, but that doesn't mean it's going to hit the ground running the instant the transformation is over. I don't know I guess to me it makes a lot of sense that to some degree her body needs like at least a few minutes to figure out how to operate itself now. Because it's just been through a massive radical species change. Not death and undeath, but things are different now. And they're not even different in the way they're supposed to be, they're their own kind of different because she's not like other vampires, that would be too easy. Like yes the transformation was the process of her body going through physical change, and now her body has changed and now her body is adjusting to being changed.","x":-83,"y":-2604,"width":543,"height":664},
		{"id":"6f1393ae6ad57b2b","type":"text","text":"The wave of nausea hit her harder and faster than usual, so much so that she almost projectile vomited right there on the floor. But Sara managed to swallowed back the acid and breath. She focused on relaxing her body, because she didn't want to lose her dinner, at least not all of it. The longer she kept it down, the more she gave her body a chance to digest it. \n\nThe weirdest part was that familiar stomach pain was finally gone, instead the feeling in her stomach was more that it was... heavy? The sensation was different, but that didn't change the task at hand, if anything this only justified it more. ","x":-12,"y":-3040,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"b430b5bdaada4b0c","type":"text","text":"- [ ] Does Sara remember biting Lilith's wrist and drinking vampire blood? ","x":1960,"y":-2030,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"ba8931403c5441ab","type":"text","text":"This time, Sara sat leaning forward on the couch across from Lilith. Her fellow vampire. She put her hand to her forehead, it was all so much to take in. \n\n![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-18-26_8-49-05%20PM.png)\n\nLilith had to admit, she was concerned about her new fledging. Vomiting wasn't normal for vampires, but she could wait until Sara was ready to talk about it. \n\nAfter a long pause, \"Is everything tasting different normal?\" Sara spoke, and then looked up at Lilith. \n\n![](../assets/img/02.04/12-12-17_7-04-23%20PM.png)\n\n\"Well of course. What humans eat won't have the same flavor. We aren't human.\" She made her tone soft. \"Even during transformation, such changes are normal.\" ","x":-948,"y":4915,"width":780,"height":1275},
		{"id":"b60fa4d5f052c3a7","type":"text","text":"Maybe later on at some point someone is talking to Sara and asking her if she misses solid food, she just sort of shrugs. \"Sometimes a little I guess. But honestly this stuff taste better than protein shakes.\" and she has a bloody mary drink in her hand. \n\nBecause to Sara, food was always fuel. It wasn't for enjoyment or pleasure. \n\nPlus, frankly it makes her diet simpler. There are no macro to track. She doesn't have to watch her protien vs her carbs. She just puts the blood fruit in the blender or juicer or whatever, and boom, everything her body need in prefect ratios. ","x":80,"y":7463,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"b156c1d781f057fd","type":"text","text":"Technically Emma's sunlight immunity could be partially due to how it was Sara that bit her? Like mostly that she's a former ghost, and ghosts can't be weak to sunlight, they're non-coporeal. But it could also be related to it being Sara that turned her. Because while generally the vampire Sara makes are normal, this is how own teenage daughter that is a former ghost. ","x":680,"y":7463,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"7126d7b8ea206df2","type":"text","text":"I'm picturing like a morning where Jane offers some of the breakfast she has made for all 4 of them. And Sara is like I'm too tired to eat right now, maybe later. \n\nLike her stomach is in pain (from the transformation), but at least she's not nauseous at the moment, and she simply doesn't have the energy to deal with needing to work at keeping herself calm and trying to prevent it from coming up, and then eventually rushing to the bathroom and such. Intense vomiting uses a lot of muscles and she's just so tired. She's not getting good sleep at all, she's just exhausted. And she just doesn't feel like dealing with it, she's miserable enough at the moment. ","x":940,"y":6343,"width":400,"height":460},
		{"id":"bce83897d8eff3e9","type":"text","text":"- [x] Withered stomach + protein shake?\n- [ ] withered stomach + bar drinks?\n- [x] what does oolong tea mug look like? \n\nThe withered stomach would not keep her from drinking protein shakes. So during the transformation, they at least went down better than food. \n\nThe mugs in the existing picture can be tea, that's what they look like in game when using the tea magic brewer object. ","x":940,"y":6870,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"8042ae7db679c773","type":"text","text":"Maybe there's a scene where she's debating rather to go back to her athletic career or not after the maternity leave is over? Like yeah she doesn't want to look like she got washed out by pregnancy, but is it really fair to enter a competition against humans when she has superhuman strength & speed? ","x":1240,"y":7463,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"8f015fd57a8b3f6d","type":"text","text":"- [ ] Sara can still workout after her transformation, and it does help with her anger, but it's not as effective since her limits are way out there now. So she needs more than only working out. \n\nI don't think the mixology is going to help her with her anger, but stuff from Jane will. ","x":1600,"y":6943,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"d08e9d8625e05d07","type":"text","text":"\"I wouldn't call is just not the same flavor. All solid food tastes so vile that it makes me gag.\" Sara couldn't help complaining. Even if it was normal, it felt so extreme. \n\n![](../assets/img/02.04/12-12-17_7-06-28%20PM.png)\n\nSara listed off things on her fingers, \"I've tried grilled cheese, salad, pancakes, sandwiches.\" Sara sighed, \"Everything solid I've managed to choke down recently, well... it doesn't stay down. And I've tried a lot different foods.\" Sara deflated a bit. \"The only things that have stayed down are liquids; I've basically been living on protein shakes, tea, and stuff like that.\" \n\n\"That's not normal,\" Lilith's eye got wider and she leaned forward in her chair. \"Things should taste different, but not vile.\"","x":-948,"y":6227,"width":780,"height":753},
		{"id":"74f28f0fbf5b3186","type":"text","text":"\"It's not supposed to be this bad?\" Sara felt conflicted again; if this wasn't normal, then was she ok? \n\n\"No, it is not. Some mild discomforting during the transformation is normal, but vampires can still eat solid food. It doesn't provide us with any nutrition, so the flavor is a little muted. But it is still overall pleasant. It certainly doesn't make our kind ill. Blending in with mortals would be challenging at times if it did.\" Lilith tried to mix concern with warmth. What was wrong with her poor fledging? Sure there were the rumors of ancient vampires with withered stomachs, but she didn't believe such nonsense. \"If you would like, I can try to use my senses to see if I can tell what's going on?\"\n\n","x":-948,"y":7060,"width":780,"height":420},
		{"id":"ec284b30a27e68d2","type":"text","text":"\"Your senses?\" But even as the question left her mouth, Sara had a feeling that she knew. \"Or... You mean like how I can feel you're both vampires, don't you?\" \n\n\"And like how you knew to come to me to answers.\" Lilith nodded. \n\nSara wanted to argue it was because she got that flashes of memory back, but she knew that wasn't all there was to it, she could sense that too. She crossed her legs. \n\n\"It's a mixture of being able to sense and feel about the physical things around you, and instinctually feeling and knowing things that are less physical.\" Lilith held out her hand as if she were holding a ball, even though it was empty. \n\n![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-18-26_8-13-02%20PM.png)\n\nSara put her arms around herself. She had used this new vampire ability without even trying; without even knowing she had it. It was kinda chilling. But she nodded, \"Yes, if you can tell what's going on, or can I sense myself?\" she wondered aloud. She couldn't at the moment, but for all she knew, she simply needed training for that.  ","x":-948,"y":7540,"width":780,"height":880},
		{"id":"a9b6d19727ae9849","type":"text","text":"Sara rushed after Lilith,\n\n![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-16-26_11-07-00%20AM.png)\n\nand barely made it in time before she was sick several times. \n\nDuring one of the pauses, she managed to herself get lowered to her knees. \n\n![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-16-26_1-14-55%20PM.png)\n\nSara held her belly with her left hand while she gripped the seat with her right to help keep herself up. More had already come up than she had expected, but she knew the feeling in her gut: it wasn't done. \n\n----\n\nAfter a few more times of puking and pauses where she tried to breath, the nauseous feeling finally passed. Sara was shaky on her feet. She grabbed the edge of the sink to help pull herself up. She used it to rinse her mouth out. Sara held the edge of the sink as she tried to breath slowly. \n\nShe felt weak as she stumbled back to the living room, and sat on the couch across from Lilith. Her fellow vampire. It was all so much to take in. ","x":4490,"y":1101,"width":780,"height":1340},
		{"id":"0e1e0193dd6df84c","type":"text","text":"\n![](../assets/img/02.04/12-12-17_7-01-00%20PM.png)\n\nSara rushed after her and barely made it in time,\n\n![](../assets/img/02.04/12-12-17_7-01-22%20PM.png)\n\nfor everything she had eaten for dinner to force it's way back out of her. As it did, her racing thoughts slowed back down. She didn't know **how** she knew it was all true, but she could feel it in her bones: not only were vampires real, she now was one. \n\nSara moved to the sink, rinsed her mouth, and gripped the sink as she tried to breath slowly. She felt weak as she stumbled back to the living room, and sat on the couch across from Lilith. Her fellow vampire. It was all so much to take in. ","x":5370,"y":1161,"width":780,"height":1160},
		{"id":"4ab3b9cf0c4b5d51","type":"text","text":"And maybe Sara and Jane weren't just ignoring this whole thing the whole time, maybe Jane like looked it up online or on her phone or something and was like yeah there is an extreme form of morning sickness, and Sara's like \"of course there is. There's an extreme version of everything that can happen to the body.\"\n\nI mean I'll need to look up how that works and what things kind of help it, but basically maybe they were treating it like it was just that like super extreme ridiculous version of morning sickness, and that's why they weren't like crazy worried about it? I mean it's concerning it's absolutely concerning, but it's not like why weren't they in the emergency room?\n\nAnd I mean maybe Sarah did see whatever sort of like medical person they have for her team or whatever sports she play, I mean surely there's some sort of medical professional around somewhere that's like not that out of the ordinary for her to see. Again professional athlete, to some degree this is an investment. Because her body is her asset that earns her income. In a more literal way than the average person. But anyway and they're like yeah sounds like whatever there's like an actual medical diagnosis for it, but they're like yeah it sounds like that stupid extreme morning sickness be really careful and maybe we're just going to put you on maternity leave early this time. We'll tell the press it's just a vacation. So that then they can write the tabloids about how you had fun on that vacation wink.","x":1250,"y":1241,"width":520,"height":720},
		{"id":"4c24fd315b18a035","type":"text","text":"Maybe Sara isn't truly \"alone\" on Lilith's bathroom floor. Maybe at some point Don &/or her coach's words come to her. Something like the stick coach where he's like \"you know this pain, you know you have to get through it.\"\n\nAnd maybe she doesn't understand why that's where her head goes until she stands up and is shaky. But her body is shifting to that \"oh good the garbage is gone\" type of state, but maybe that's not how her mind interprets it. Maybe to her it's familiar because it reminds her of after a hard workout. I mean it's obviously not exactly the same, but she's shaky and tired but she feels better now. \n\nAs Sara stood there, gripping the sink and trying to breathe, it was like as if something had finally clicked into place.","x":589,"y":1336,"width":455,"height":531},
		{"id":"68dd03bf011bcae0","type":"text","text":"So I'm looking at this and I'm thinking about the stuff below. \n\nSara might not need space after she's sick, because she might not actually be upset about throwing up. That might not really bother her so much because of reasons in other cards. \n\nI mean sure she's reeling from the whole I'm a vampire now thing, but that's a different type of issue. It's more about having her sense of reality suddenly changed, and her natural affinity for the dark power is kind of forcing this realization to happen faster than it would otherwise. ","x":690,"y":2158,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"32793ded4ce8f81d","type":"text","text":"This is clearing her withered stomach (and/or entire withered gut) so it can take in blood. So once it's empty, she probably feels a lot better before too long. And this means her thirst can come online. Where as before, all this stuff it couldn't even pass let alone digest was in the way. \n\nSo of course she starts to feel better. Her body has gotten rid of the stuff that isn't food to her. ","x":1550,"y":2631,"width":660,"height":244},
		{"id":"bf59a27a96bb6e8b","type":"text","text":"Her stomach has finished withering because her transformation is over. Her stomach not in the in between type of state, where it's still changing from the transformation (which even in normal situations is very painful).\n\nI'm thinking that during the transformation, her body was basically confused as this slow \"crash\" happened. \n\nThe vampire transformation is supposed to convert the digestive track to be able to use blood to keep the body alive. But because of the pregnancy, the transformation didn't happen in the normal fashion. Between the hormones and the altered needs/demands on her body and the dark magic, her biological \"wires\" got crossed. Like two medications having an interaction, even when the person can take both separately. I mean sure her affinity for the dark power played a role, a nature/nurture mix (or \"prefect storm\"). \n\nBut once her transformation is complete, her stomach has firmly \"made up it's mind\" on what her body needs. It's not half in half out, or half wanting blood and half wanting food (while only taking in food and not being fully able to digest it). It wants blood and it's rejecting everything solid. Decision made. \n\nHer body isn't trying to digest the food anymore. Before it sort of could, so it sort of was. But only sort of, it also sort of wasn't, and that's why she was throwing up so often. It had to do something with the parts it couldn't deal with, so it vomited them back up. While also trying to digest the parts it could. \n\nBut now, none of that trying to digest & reject at the same time stuff. Her gut says it's all got to go. While the removal process isn't comfortable, it does get her body to a point where her gut is ok with things again. Before it was trying to do both and once so it never reached a sort of \"all done, happy with things now\" point, because there wasn't one in this sort of stalemate tug of war. But the transformation finished and the chaos is gone. \n\nSo while for a minute her gut is really upset about the food in her, once it's gone, things finally settle for the first time since before this all started.","x":1550,"y":2920,"width":660,"height":871},
		{"id":"e20f3f4d4d84a7a3","type":"text","text":"Though, to be clear, this is not the vampire side winning. There's a saying that war doesn't have winners, just survivors. That is the sort of thing we're looking at here. She's had 2 opposite contradictory processes happening to her body at the same time for the first trimester of her pregnancy. The pregnancy has been driving a need to digest food while trying to make it's own changes (cravings, morning sickness, slowed digestion, and all the usual things pregnancy does) while the vampire magic has been fundamentally rebuilding her body into the powering magical being she is becoming. But this isn't resolved by the vampire side winning. The vampire side does not trash the gut. Normal vampires can eat regular human food if they want to, no issues at all (they don't even have to choke it down, they can just eat it, and it tastes fine; nothing really tastes amazing to them, but it certainly doesn't taste like cardboard, things just taste okay instead of delicious). This is like a drug interaction that has left behind permanent organ damage even after the drugs have cleared the system. \n\nOh and even the pregnancy hasn't been a stable thing. Sara's unborn child, Anne is transformed too. Sara doesn't know it when she knocks on Lilith's door, but she is a vampire pregnant with a vampire. \n\nSo not only was there what normal pregnancy does to a human body, and not only was there what a typical vampire transformation involves going on, and not only where the two interacting badly, on top of all of that, the fetus was undue going a vampire transformation process. It all contributed to Sara's transformation ending with her stomach withering. As far as why she didn't puke her guts out when the black smoke took her, idk, it needing just a bit of time checks out for me? Like sure her body is done changing, but it still need to figure out how to operate itself. And the emotional turmoil helps it along there. ","x":1550,"y":3918,"width":660,"height":680},
		{"id":"f2ab7aa8ae26ba0c","type":"text","text":"Maybe some vampires get their \"vampire taste buds\" while they're transforming and some get them when the transformation is over. \n\nSara got something else entirely. And maybe once she's transformed, food tastes even worse (not that she's inclined to taste it ever again). I mean there is that omelet she makes for Jane, and maybe she tried licking something to make sure it tasted fine, and had to go rinse her tongue? Though making an omelet doesn't require tasting it? Maybe her sense of smell is off? Or maybe it's just been while so she's rusty and isn't sure if she remembered all the steps because Jane has been handling the cooking? ","x":2310,"y":2789,"width":400,"height":528},
		{"id":"1c597003476b819a","type":"text","text":"The notes about Sara's gut calming down is not the vampire side winning. There's a saying that \"war doesn't have winners, just survivors.\" - That is the sort of thing we're looking at here. She's had 2 opposite contradictory processes happening to her body at the same time for the first trimester of her pregnancy. The pregnancy has been driving a need to digest food while trying to make it's own changes (cravings, morning sickness, slowed digestion, and all the usual things pregnancy does) while the vampire magic has been fundamentally rebuilding her body into the powering magical being she is becoming. But this isn't resolved by the vampire side winning. The vampire side does not trash her gut, both things going at once did. Normal vampires can eat regular human food if they want to, no issues at all (they don't even have to choke it down, they can just eat it, and it tastes fine; nothing really tastes amazing to them, but it certainly doesn't taste like cardboard, things just taste okay instead of delicious). This is like a drug interaction that has left behind permanent organ damage even after the drugs have cleared the system. \n\nOh and even the pregnancy hasn't been a stable thing either. Sara's unborn child, Anne is transformed by this too. Sara doesn't know it when she knocks on Lilith's door, but she is a vampire pregnant with a vampire at that point.  \n\nSo not only was there what normal pregnancy does to a human body, and not only was there what a typical vampire transformation involves going on, and not only where the two interacting badly, on top of all of that, the fetus was undergoing a vampire transformation process. It all contributed to Sara's transformation ending with her stomach withering. As far as why she didn't puke her guts out when the black smoke took her & the transformation completed, idk. It needing just a bit of time just this once checks out for me? Like sure her body is done changing, but it still needs to figure out how to operate itself. And maybe the emotional turmoil helps it along there a little sooner? \n\nSo like I said the main thing I want to clarify is that this is not the vampire side winning the war, this is her stomach being a destroyed battlefield after a war. If the vampire side had won she might have lost the pregnancy, but her stomach definitely would not have withered. Nothing won. That's where the drug interaction metaphor comes in, these are two things that should not be done at the same time because there are permanent consequences that would not happen if they were done at different times. But not all the consequences are bad, Anne is born a day walker. She's a full vampire, but she lacks weaknesses. Please focus on when Sara and Lilith are talking because Sara has sought out Lilith and Sara has just finished her transformation and is a vampire. There’s a few different version of this chapter (2.4), including one that’s a txt that’s a renamed obsidian canvas file, so it’s especially mess (don’t worry about the card ID numbers, obsidian doesn’t show them so you don’t need to mention them or even say you’re not going to mention them), but the content is plain text.  I’ve added some new notes looking at what sort of mental state Sara, as a pro athlete, would be in and how she would respond to this. There’s also some revision notes at the start of 2.5 that are related to this plot/arc. What parts do you like best? How do you think Sara is going to respond to this? Do the notes about body discomfort not getting to her that much make sense? \n\nThere's something else I want to clarify: The notes about Sara gut calming down is not the vampire side winning. There's a saying that war doesn't have winners, just survivors. That is the sort of thing we're looking at here. She's had 2 opposite contradictory processes happening to her body at the same time for the first trimester of her pregnancy. The pregnancy has been driving a need to digest food while trying to make it's own changes (cravings, morning sickness, slowed digestion, and all the usual things pregnancy does) while the vampire magic","x":2330,"y":3718,"width":580,"height":760},
		{"id":"d37a0e4788757bdf","type":"text","text":"Yes not being able to workout gets to her, but she uses exercise to regulate her emotions, especially her anger. \n\nShe is a hot head, but because she works out, she's not an angry person. Take away the exercise, and she at least has a much harder time not being angry. ","x":-130,"y":2953,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"33d6a28e237adfdd","type":"text","text":"Should Sara have bandages sometimes? Or if I can find a knee brace mod, maybe she sometimes wears one when she pulls something? \n\nTo help visually show this? \n\nOh maybe there's ice pack or ice bath mods???","x":290,"y":3598,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"ee6d9b3aa574258f","type":"text","text":"Sara is a professional athlete. Pain and discomfort are part of her world. I mean yes she tries to avoid injuries, but I'm not sure pro's actually can avoid at least some discomfort? Insert the movie Stick It where she talks about peeling callouses the size of quarters off your fingers or is a lot of pain from being sore form taking a break in her training. At the very least, the being sore part I know is true. Heck I started taking short walks and one of my heels wasn't happy about it for a day or two. So even if she doesn't get like a broken leg or anything serious like that, surely at least minor discomfort is just part of the package? And probably more the minor. She's someone who is in touch with her body, she would have to be, and she used to it not feeling well sometimes. Plus she probably know staying calm helps? So maybe she's not that emotional upset over who she physically feels. Though she is needing a moment to process being a vampire","x":410,"y":2753,"width":460,"height":601},
		{"id":"79183229a38ea651","type":"text","text":"Given her new vampire state (fully transformed), while throwing up might feel worse as it's happening, but honestly she would probably feel much better pretty soon after it's over. \n\nFor one thing, now that she is actually a vampire, her hunger is gone. Like gone gone. \n\nThe food leaving her body might even feel different. As a human, food is supposed to stay down. As a vampire, isn't not something her body needs. ","x":950,"y":2753,"width":400,"height":600},
		{"id":"4ecd540ed7bf5c01","type":"text","text":"Her stomach collateral damage \n\nIt was like a tug of war, but no one won, the rope snapped. ","x":1020,"y":3598,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"62121f3f1abbdc95","type":"text","text":"I mean she's going to be on leave from work anyway from the pregnancy, it would make sense for her to stop and look at what she wants to do with her life now. Like literally what species she is has just changed. If ever there is a time for soul searching, that's it. Plus the culinary career is indoors, and she gets off work after sundown. That's relevant. Sure she's not like super weak to the sun, but she isn't immune either. \n\nAnd maybe the bloody mary drink idea kinda has her going in that direction? Idk, I guess I want this to make sense because this is what happened in the save file. The sim Sara got to Rookie in the athletic career, and then switched to the culinary career path, and that's part of why they started having bars in every kitchen in the house. Like I built that kitchen themed with decor to match the best bar in the game. That wasn't easy, since it's tiki themed and most of the kitchen objects in the game aren't. ","x":1370,"y":101,"width":680,"height":880},
		{"id":"130bfe72d75c2bb0","type":"text","text":"Building on that if she had to learn some mindfulness exercises with Jane's help during her first pregnancy, that could basically be where her head space is now, I'm just trying to breathe just trying to relax, as an athlete she probably has a higher pain tolerance and has a completely different mindset when it comes to pain, so she's not freaking out about the physical sensations the discomfort and the pain, and she could be trying to in this pregnancy use the stuff that helped her some in the last pregnancy, maybe she could still work out more in the last one? Because regular human, where is this one she's had the fucking tug of war from hell inside her. And that could all relate back to later with Cassandra, and helping her with the werewolf fury. Because also eventually she's going to switch away from the pro athlete career and into the culinary career, so she's going to need to work on that whole using other things to manage her anchor. Not that she can't use punching anymore, but things are going to change. That has a certain sort of irony to it though, going into food service when she can't eat. But it's actually someone who's been in food service it's actually more convenient that way if you don't need to eat.\n\nWell it could be that she's just working up the ranks to become a mixologist, because what she's actually interested in his bartending, because well it's the only thing she can have now? I don't know that feels like a really weird pivot that doesn't really that math don't math I don't know or maybe it does I'm really unsure about that. Because like she was so committed to being an athlete, and exercise has been such a big part of her life, but like at the same time that was only to manage her anger and thanks to her pregnancies she probably learned to not need as much exercise, also she's a vampire so like her life has taken a sharp right turn no left turn those are more violent and dangerous. Like I mean who's to say she could even pass basic physicals as vampire? Also it's not really a competition if you literally have superhuman abilities.  ","x":511,"y":301,"width":611,"height":800},
		{"id":"2ca47bc7878094f6","type":"text","text":"I don't want working out to becomes useless to her once she's a vampire, maybe it's more like she needs to approach it differently. Like when she was a human teenager, maybe she could just go for a run and that was enough to cause the full regulation, that was enough activity to scale down her activation, but as a young adult vampire, while the activity still helps it doesn't de-escalate everything on its own, maybe she has to bring the more mindfulness and what not into her workouts, like still punching, but really honing into her body and really paying attention to how that feels while she's punching. Like it necessitates more mind body connection to work, and maybe she supplements the workouts with like meditating or whatever.\n\nMaybe she also has control over her strength. Because vampires that have the speed can choose to walk at a normal human sim pace. Maybe it's about how much she uses the dark power while she's running or punching or lifting. She against there's more of a mind-body connection required to make this work for her. She can choose how she mixes the ratio of her supernatural abilities with her her own muscles, if she's in tune with her body & is paying attention & such. ","x":2290,"y":261,"width":680,"height":560},
		{"id":"1231a37daafe6f2c","type":"text","text":"Which again just feed back into that idea that in strangerville at some point she's going to need to scan herself (sense her own body), and it's going to temporary mess up her mind-body connection, and that is going to affect her. \n\nLike yes she will have the wounds from the fight, but her carefully built internal harmony is going to get smashed to pieces, and rebuilding it is going to be hard. \n\n\"Look, I get why you put on a front around them, but you don't need to put on a brave face around me. Something is off about you.\" Don said. \"So what's going on?\"","x":3150,"y":341,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"27a5795745c01890","type":"text","text":"Maybe Sara **needs** to sit, like her body is wiped after what it just went through, but she doesn't want to face these near strangers. But maybe she can tell Lilith isn't in the parlor anymore?\n\nOr maybe she comes out there, and Lilith can tell she needs a minute, so Lilith makes up some excuse to leave?\n\nSara sat across from Lilith, her fellow vampire. It was all too much to take in. \n\nLilith take a breath as she focused her dark magic, \"I know this is quite improper, but would it bother you if I \"","x":-110,"y":5735,"width":780,"height":400},
		{"id":"1c1a75d5dc51b72e","type":"text","text":"Lilith kinda ignores her being sick? Lilith would be able to hear it, and I mean Sara said that what was happening. \n\nMaybe it works better without Lilith asking if she's ok, not because she doesn't care, but because Lilith is a bit confused, and Sara seems distressed, and well this is a lot to take in. Maybe Lilith can sense that Sara needs a moment. ","x":-1960,"y":4915,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"d36dd91bf9687e92","type":"text","text":"Lilith had to admit, that was concerning. Vomiting wasn't normal for vampires, but she could also feel that her new fledgling needed some space or needed a moment. I don't know I guess I'm not sure how to phrase that, and I mean maybe it's not purely a dark sense thing, because it doesn't fully read emotions, it can tell certain things but it's not mind reading. But at the same time maybe Lilith can tell from Sara's body language? ","x":-1540,"y":5055,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"0936e62aaa285664","type":"text","text":"\"Are you ok?\" Lilith seemed genuine, and trustworthy... somehow. \n\nNot sure what to say, Sara went back to the beginning. \"I guess it started with things tasting different.\" \n\n![](../assets/img/02.04/12-12-17_7-04-23%20PM.png)\n\n\"Well of course. What humans eat won't have the same flavor. We aren't human.\" Lilith's tone was soft and caring. \"Even during transformation, such changes are normal.\"","x":-2880,"y":5345,"width":780,"height":620},
		{"id":"1284b5375c758530","type":"text","text":"So here's Lilith is kinda thinking like \"so that's where she wants to start?\" Maybe Lilith can feel that Sara doesn't want to talk about pukling her guts out. ","x":-1760,"y":5602,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"2738239510d4d27f","type":"text","text":"Tonight was the first time in weeks that her stomach didn't hurt. ","x":-1380,"y":6260,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"211ec92f767bed8b","type":"text","text":"\"But I have heard tales, rumors. Some say that a few of the very oldest vampires have stomachs that have withered. They say that these vampires are so deeply in touch with the dark power that, after centuries, they permanently lost their ability to keep down anything solid.\" Lilith paused, \"You have such a strong natural affinity for the dark power... have you been pregnant through at least most of your transformation?\"","x":-2460,"y":7033,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"e97cb66e1fc90ee7","type":"text","text":"\"What you're describing, it reminds me of some rumors I've heard. Some claim that a few of the very oldest vampires have an aversion to eating solid food. That, over the centuries, they gained such an affinity for the dark power of the vampires that their stomach shived up and withered. Leaving them dependent on blood.\" ","x":-2060,"y":7033,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"69c717d54f224df3","type":"text","text":"It may not be quite as delicious, but I'll have some cheesecake now and then.\"\n\n\n\n\"Most vampires can still eat solid human food. It doesn't taste as wonderful as before the change, or provide any real nutrition, but the flavor is... ok.\" Lilith shrugged, \"But eating doesn't cause... problems. It helps us keep up appearances, blend in among mortals.\"\n\nSara simply waited for Lilith to continue; *most* implied *not all*.\n\n\"But I have heard tales, well rumors, similar to what you are describing. Some say that of the very oldest ancient vampires have a strong aversion to solid food. The rumors say that, over the centuries, they have developed such an affinity for the dark power of the vampires, that their stomachs have withered. Which causes them to permanently lose their ability to keep down anything solid, according to these rumors.\" Lilith held out a hand, \"If you would like, I can try to use my senses to see if I can tell what's going on?\"","x":-1560,"y":7160,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"1d06ff80ccddb2ad","type":"text","text":"If Lilith can sense Sara, is the bond between a maker and a vampire akin to like a mother? Or is it very different in nature? \n\nI don't know part of me is thinking about having Lilith waiting outside bathroom door, to help Sarah back to the couch\n\nAnd part of me thinking about maybe Sarah can get to the couch by herself. She's a little shaky for a moment, but as the pain passes, her vampire body is still able to move and such. And maybe having Sarah sitting there on the couch, and thinking it was weird. It was also overwhelming and she had the feeling like she just wanted to be alone, but somehow Lilith being there didn't bother her. As if she already was alone? It did make sense. ","x":-110,"y":5300,"width":780,"height":400},
		{"id":"ce6914bd65538672","type":"text","text":"Lilith shook her head. \"You can't sense your own body. Your own mind will get in the way. Vampiric sensing relies of being in tune with the darkness. But feeling your own body, there's a reflex to use your nerve endings, which confuses everything unless you force yourself to ignore that. But ignoring your own nervous system would come at a cost, you don't want to lose your mind-body connection.\" ","x":-948,"y":8520,"width":780,"height":280},
		{"id":"066231c87565821a","type":"text","text":"\"No I don't.\" That was the last thing Sara want to do. \"It doesn't pose any risk to pregnancy, does it?\" So many scans and procedures at a human hospital did. \n\n\"No, it's just as safe as me looking at you as I am now.\"\n\nSara nodded, \"So, how do you sense me? How does this work?\" \n\n\"I need to be physically close to you, it will be best if you let me touch your midsection. And I'm better at it if I'm in my dark form.\"\n\nSara nodded, and stood. \"Ok let's do this.\"\n\nLilith stood as well, and focused to call on the dark power, to draw it to herself. \n\nSara not only say the dark magic surround Lilith, she felt it. \n\n![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-18-26_9-57-37%20PM.png)\n\nOnce she changed, Lilith asked, \"Are you ready?\"\n\nThe glowing purple eyes were unsetting, but this was far from the first medical exam that made Sara wasn't looking forward to. \"Yes.\" She needed answers. ","x":-948,"y":8900,"width":780,"height":1040},
		{"id":"83d5d21103e88f7b","type":"text","text":"Sara swallowed, and looked down at her midsection. So her gut was trashed? For good? But she was still pregnant, her belly was clearly growing, and she needed to feed both of them... to feed. She was a *vampire* that needed to *feed*. \"So, are you saying I need to drink blood then?\" At first thought made her skin crawl. But as she pictured doing so, a thirsty hunger awoke within her. One that made the idea sound so wonderful... that part of her body shivered. Sara wasn't sure rather it was from disgust, fear, or... desire. \n\n\"The rumors say that fresh blood is the only thing those vampires can only consume, but I don't know if that's true. It is rumors.\" ","x":-1148,"y":11280,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"0300ff78b7115cd5","type":"text","text":"It wouldn't be the first time Sara had needed to make major changes to her diet, but it would certainly be.... different. \n\n","x":-680,"y":11280,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"bb9f7e7e97bc49fd","type":"text","text":"\"Maybe... I guess?\" Sara's reply was uneasy. She didn't actually know when each had started, but somehow she felt 'yes' was the right answer. \n\n\"That is...\" Lilith paused, \"unusual. I'm not aware of anyone who turned while with child. I don't know if the two could have interacted in some way? And together caused your insides to wither.\"","x":-1240,"y":11800,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"1a90bf367c92d3ce","type":"text","text":"![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-18-26_9-59-35%20PM.png)\n\nLilith got quiet and seemed to be deep in concentrating. Part of Sara thought it was odd having someone she barely knew close like this, but part of her was just fine with it. Lilith didn't feel as much like a stranger as she should have, and Sara realized she knew she could trust Lilith. \n\nAfter a few moments, \"Oh... I see.\" Lilith closed her eyes, lowered her hands to her sides, and took a deep breath.\n\n\"What is it?\"\n\n\"Let us sit. This will take some explaining.\" \n\n----\n\n\"Yes...\" Lilith paused. \"your stomach has withered, and is in bad shape. It needs... nothing solid. No surprises there... As far as why, let's see here. Ah, right there. Yes, I see. It was the combination. Transformation and pregnancy, I suppose you could say it's like an interaction.\" Lilith closed her eyes, lowered her hands, and took a deep breath. \"I'm sorry, that's all I can sense for now.\"\n\n\"Can you explain a bit, I don't follow.\"\n\n\"The two process are opposite in nature.\"\n\n----\n\n\"I'm not sure I get what you mean by interaction. Has it hurt the baby?\"\n\n\"No, she is fine. A bit thirsty, but new vampires sometimes are. ","x":-948,"y":10080,"width":780,"height":1100},
		{"id":"8a5f549de2916759","type":"text","text":"![](Sims4-Yootz-Story/assets/img/02.04/06-18-26_9-59-03%20PM.png)","x":0,"y":10400,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"cefcdd7ed9bce265","type":"text","text":"I like this, because in time, Sara can learn to override the conscious mind part, to actually feel the darkness instead of her nerves when she wants to. Though it will be tricky and come with meaning she needs (at least?) a moment to listen to her nerves again. It's not necessarily good for her to disconnect from her nervous system, but maybe it's necessary alone in Strangerville? Once Don is infected she is functionally alone.","x":-40,"y":8480,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"8b519124b755dc3d","type":"text","text":" and took some more deep slow breaths","x":-1500,"y":2854,"width":400,"height":400}
	],
